{
  "texts": [
    "The roadmap of LLM-enhanced KGs (LEK).",
    "Event extraction involves automatically identifying events and related information from text, including triggers, entities, and key details like time and location.",
    "This forms the basis for constructing event KGs, such as EventKG (Gottschalk and Demidova, 2018).",
    "EvIT (Tao et al., 2024) trains LLMs through event-oriented instruction tuning and uses a heuristic unsupervised method to mine event quadruples from large-scale corpora.",
    "Chen R. et al. (2024) uses LLMs as expert annotators to extract event information from sentences and generate augmented datasets aligned with baseline distributions."
  ]
}